The paper deals with the problem of counting triangulations and other crossing-free structures on a set of points in the plane. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve dynamic programming and divide-and-conquer, which are common in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the approximation ratio of the algorithm, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
